¹ There is some perplexity occa- sioned by the use of this designa- tion. Stephen de Bulmer was 5011 of Radrssphus, and grandson of Ber- tram de Bulmer. He married Emma, daughter of William de Turberville, and by her had issue, John, Thomas, and Hugh. John was succeeded by his son J ohn; he again by another John3 and this last by a fourth John, who succeeded to the wilton (in Cleveland) inheritance on the death, without offspring, of Thomas, the grandson of Stephen's brother Alan. It is hard to see, then, in what sense Thomas de Muschamps is described as heir of Stephen de Bulmer. That there was a connec- tion between the Bulmers and Mus- champs is probable.
